sequenceDiagram
    participant Winner as 👤 Winner
    participant UI as ⚛️ Web App
    participant RuleAPI as 📜 Rule API
    participant Judge as ⚖️ Judge API
    participant LLM as 🤖 LLM Service
    participant WS as 🔌 WebSocket
    participant DB as 🗄️ Database
    
    Note over Winner,DB: Rule Compilation Flow
    
    Winner->>UI: Round won - prompted to propose rule
    UI->>Winner: Show rule proposal form
    
    Winner->>UI: Enter rule description<br/>"Players must say 'Have a nice day' when playing a 7"
    Winner->>UI: Select priority (50)
    Winner->>UI: Select category (speech)
    Winner->>UI: Click "Submit Rule"
    
    UI->>UI: Validate input<br/>(10-1000 chars, priority 1-100)
    
    UI->>RuleAPI: POST /games/{id}/rules<br/>{description, priority, category}
    
    RuleAPI->>DB: Create rule record<br/>(status: proposed)
    DB-->>RuleAPI: Rule created {ruleId}
    
    RuleAPI->>WS: Publish rule.proposed event
    RuleAPI-->>UI: 201 Created {rule}
    
    UI->>UI: Show "Compiling..." state
    WS-->>UI: rule.proposed event
    
    RuleAPI->>Judge: POST /compile<br/>{ruleId, description, priority, category}
    
    RuleAPI->>DB: Update rule status<br/>(status: compiling)
    RuleAPI->>WS: Publish rule.compiling event
    WS-->>UI: rule.compiling event
    
    Judge->>Judge: Parse natural language
    Judge->>WS: Publish compilation.progress<br/>(stage: parsing, 25%)
    WS-->>UI: Show progress: "Parsing..."
    
    Judge->>LLM: Analyze rule intent<br/>Extract triggers, conditions, actions
    LLM-->>Judge: Structured rule components
    
    Judge->>WS: Publish compilation.progress<br/>(stage: analyzing, 50%)
    WS-->>UI: Show progress: "Analyzing..."
    
    Judge->>Judge: Generate executable format<br/>(triggers, conditions, actions, penalties)
    
    Judge->>WS: Publish compilation.progress<br/>(stage: generating, 75%)
    WS-->>UI: Show progress: "Generating..."
    
    Judge->>DB: Query existing rules<br/>for conflict detection
    DB-->>Judge: Active rules
    
    Judge->>Judge: Check for conflicts<br/>Identify ambiguities
    
    Judge->>WS: Publish compilation.progress<br/>(stage: validating, 90%)
    WS-->>UI: Show progress: "Validating..."
    
    Judge->>DB: Store compiled rule
    DB-->>Judge: Compiled rule saved
    
    Judge-->>RuleAPI: 200 OK<br/>{compiledRule, conflicts, ambiguities}
    
    RuleAPI->>DB: Update rule status<br/>(status: review)
    RuleAPI->>WS: Publish rule.compiled event
    WS-->>UI: rule.compiled event
    
    UI->>Winner: Show compiled rule for review<br/>- Triggers: card_played (rank=7)<br/>- Actions: require_speech("Have a nice day")<br/>- Penalty: 1 card
    
    alt Winner approves
        Winner->>UI: Click "Approve"
        UI->>RuleAPI: PATCH /games/{id}/rules/{ruleId}<br/>{status: approved, feedback}
        
        RuleAPI->>DB: Update rule status<br/>(status: approved)
        RuleAPI->>WS: Publish rule.approved event
        
        RuleAPI->>DB: Update rule status<br/>(status: active)
        RuleAPI->>WS: Publish rule.activated event<br/>(with cryptic announcement)
        
        RuleAPI-->>UI: 200 OK {rule}
        WS-->>UI: rule.activated event
        
        UI->>Winner: Show "Rule activated!"
        UI->>UI: Display cryptic announcement<br/>to all players
        
    else Winner rejects
        Winner->>UI: Click "Reject"<br/>Provide reason
        UI->>RuleAPI: PATCH /games/{id}/rules/{ruleId}<br/>{status: rejected, reason}
        
        RuleAPI->>DB: Update rule status<br/>(status: rejected)
        RuleAPI->>WS: Publish rule.rejected event
        
        RuleAPI-->>UI: 200 OK {rule}
        WS-->>UI: rule.rejected event
        
        UI->>Winner: Show "Rule rejected"<br/>Option to try again
    end
    
    Note over Winner,DB: Rule is now active and will be enforced by Judge